# output_view_modes.scn — O2 Output-window aspect-correct view + Fit/1:1 live tooth.
#
# The Output window's preview used to be a bare `ImGui::Image(tex, avail)` that STRETCHED the
# 512x512 render to fill the content region (柏為's "拉視窗畫面變扁"). O2 replaces it with a
# port of TiXL ImageOutputCanvas: a uniform-scale fit (aspect preserved -> letterbox/pillarbox)
# plus Fit / 1:1 view-mode buttons + pan/zoom + a WxH x-scale overlay.
#
# This scenario proves the new toolbar is LIVE and that the two view modes actually change the
# displayed scale (so the picture differs on screen), through the real imgui draw path.
#
# RED proof:
#   - revert output_window.cpp to the bare `ImGui::Image(tex, avail)` -> the output_fit_btn /
#     output_pixel_btn map entries vanish -> the assert_map_has lines go RED.
#   - make Fit and 1:1 set the same scale (e.g. drop setPixelScale / never re-fit) -> the
#     fit-vs-pixel frame `assert_diff` goes RED (frames byte-identical).

open app/testdata/compound_smoke.swproj
wait 0.5

# The new view-mode toolbar exists (Pin + Fit + 1:1 are all recorded by eye::recordItem).
assert_map_has output_pin_btn
echo pin-button-present
assert_map_has output_fit_btn
echo fit-button-present
assert_map_has output_pixel_btn
echo pixel-button-present

# Fit mode: aspect-correct fit-to-window. Capture the fitted frame.
do click @output_fit_btn
wait 0.6
capture full fit_frame
echo captured-fit-frame

# 1:1 (Pixel) mode: native-pixel scale (x1.00). The render is drawn at a DIFFERENT scale, so the
# whole-window frame must differ from the fitted one. Aspect stays preserved in both (the fit math
# uses a single uniform scale) — what changes is the size, proving the view mode is live.
do click @output_pixel_btn
wait 0.6
assert_diff fit_frame
echo pixel-frame-differs-from-fit
